<span id="freeTextContainer12840216756726884939"><strong>DNF @ 103 pages.</strong><br/><br/>The novel really isn&apos;t working for me. The premise is interesting, but the writing so far reads as shallow and cheesy; and all the characters come across as juvenile, which is an odd feeling when they are supposed to work in law enforcement. Zoe, especially, is introduced as an expert in her field, but she sounds like a total hack most of the time. It&apos;s very hard to believe her observations have any value when she whips them out without having investigated... much of anything, re</span>
  <span id="freeText12840216756726884939" style="display:none"><strong>DNF @ 103 pages.</strong><br /><br />The novel really isn't working for me. The premise is interesting, but the writing so far reads as shallow and cheesy; and all the characters come across as juvenile, which is an odd feeling when they are supposed to work in law enforcement. Zoe, especially, is introduced as an expert in her field, but she sounds like a total hack most of the time. It's very hard to believe her observations have any value when she whips them out without having investigated... much of anything, really.</span>
